
AR12 - Constructing the view

This section explores a creative process in which architectural representation becomes a genuine narrative tool. Using digital techniques ranging from Photoshop collage to Cinema 4D rendering, each work was produced as part of Philipp Schaerer's 'Constructing the View' course at EPFL.

The collages and digital compositions combine to question and transcend conventional modes of representation, while the Cinema 4D renders emphasise attention to texture, light and spatial staging.

Together, these works highlight a commitment to exploring the possibilities offered by the image in the context of architecture.